 performed them to improve his punching power. From this, it was named the Mike Tyson push-up. Its also said that Tyson did 500 repetitions daily.","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https://www.endomondo.com/training/mike-tyson-push-ups-benefits#faq-question-1727686217547","position":3,"url":"https://www.endomondo.com/training/mike-tyson-push-ups-benefits#faq-question-1727686217547","name":"Are Mike Tyson push-ups good for beginners?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Mike Tyson push-ups are classed as an advanced push-up variation. Beginners should have mastered the normal push-up technique first for them to be good. Alongside this, they need a certain amount of core stability and mobility.","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https://www.endomondo.com/training/mike-tyson-push-ups-benefits#faq-question-1727686231859","position":4,"url":"https://www.endomondo.com/training/mike-tyson-push-ups-benefits#faq-question-1727686231859","name":"Can Mike Tyson push-ups improve my cardio?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"They use a dynamic movement pattern meaning that they do have a cardio element. However, they should be used as more of a full-body conditioning exercise rather than a cardio workout. Add them alongside dedicated cardio work.","inLanguage":"en-US"},"inLanguage":"en-US"},{"@type":"Question","@id":"https://www.endomondo.com/training/mike-tyson-push-ups-benefits#faq-question-1727686262654","position":5,"url":"https://www.endomondo.com/training/mike-tyson-push-ups-benefits#faq-question-1727686262654","name":"Can Mike Tyson push-ups help me lose weight?","answerCount":1,"acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The dynamic, full-body movement requires effort to perform correctly. Because of this, they can theoretically burn a good amount of calories. When performed alongside the right diet and other exercises, they can be used to lose weight.